# 3. System Objectives

The NEO system was designed to solve five aerospace problems:

### Problem 1

Massive heat loss.

Typical engines reject enormous thermal energy.

NEO attempts to reclaim part of it.

---

### Problem 2

Propulsion inefficiency.

Thrust normally leaves the engine and is lost.

NEO attempts to redirect useful portions.

---

### Problem 3

Structural instability.

Aircraft consume energy fighting turbulence.

NEO converts energy into stabilization.

---

### Problem 4

Fuel dependency.

Recovered energy reduces required fuel expenditure.

---

### Problem 5

Energy compartmentalization.

Traditional systems operate independently.

NEO integrates them.

