# 4. Major Subsystems

---

## A. Thermal Recovery Core (TRC)

### Function

Captures waste heat generated by propulsion systems.

### Inputs

```text
Exhaust Heat
Engine Heat
Boundary Layer Heat
Structural Heat
```

### Outputs

```text
Electrical Energy
Thermal Reservoir Energy
Secondary Propulsion Energy
```

### Components

* Thermal Capture Chamber
* Heat Exchange Matrix
* Recovery Routing Controller
* Thermal Buffer Reservoir

---

## B. Air Compression Vector Layer (ACVL)

### Function

Uses controlled airflow compression for thrust enhancement.

### Process

```text
Air Intake
     ↓
Compression
     ↓
Vector Routing
     ↓
Directed Thrust
```

### Components

* Compression Channel
* Vector Nozzle Array
* Dynamic Pressure Controller
* Flow Synchronizer

---

## C. Hydraulic Stabilization Ring (HSR)

### Function

Transforms fluid pressure into structural stabilization.

### Responsibilities

* Vibration suppression
* Turbulence mitigation
* Structural balancing
* Load equalization

---

### Core Components

```text
Hydraulic Ring
Pressure Reservoir
Stabilization Controller
Adaptive Dampers
```

